Metabolitesâ€¦Back to basics..with LME

Julin Maloof

07/26/2022

Take a different approach with metabolites:

  1. ID metabolites responding to microbes
  2. Ask if those are associated with leaf length

This is like script 12 but will use LME for block. (And fixed effect for GT?)

DONâ€™T USE THIS. GENERALLY DOES NOT IMPROVE ON SIMPLE LM MODEL. GO WITH SIMPLER MODEL.

get block info

blockinfo <- readxl::read_excel("../../plant/input/exp1_leaf_ln_data.xlsx", sheet = 2) %>%
  select(pot, block) %>%
  mutate(pot=as.character(pot),
         pot=str_pad(pot, 3, pad = "0"),
         block=str_c("block_", block))

get and wrangle metabolite data

met_raw <-read_csv("../input/metabolites_set1.csv")

Delimiter: ","

â„¹ Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.

met <- met_raw %>% 
  mutate(pot=str_pad(pot, width = 3, pad = "0")) %>%
  mutate(sampleID=str_c("wyo", genotype, pot, sep="_")) %>%
  mutate(trt=ifelse(is.na(autoclave), "BLANK", autoclave)) %>%
  select(pot, sampleID, genotype, tissue, trt, sample_mass = `sample_mass mg`, !submission_number:concatenate)  %>%
  
  #bring in block info
  left_join(blockinfo, by="pot") %>%
  
  #bring in leaf length
  left_join({leaflength %>% select(sampleID, leaf_avg_std)}) %>%
  select(sampleID, block, genotype, tissue, trt, leaf_avg_std, everything()) %>%
  
  #make long
  pivot_longer(!sampleID:sample_mass, names_to = "metabolite", values_to = "met_amount") %>%
  
  #filter away unnamed
  filter(str_detect(metabolite, pattern="^[0-9]+$", negate=TRUE)) %>%
  
  #adjust by sample mass
  mutate(met_per_mg=met_amount/sample_mass) %>%
  
  #scale and center
  group_by(metabolite, genotype, tissue) %>%
  mutate(met_per_mg=scale(met_per_mg),
         met_amt=scale(met_amount)
  ) %>% 
  pivot_wider(id_cols = c(sampleID, block, genotype, trt, leaf_avg_std), 
              names_from = c(tissue, metabolite), 
              values_from = starts_with("met_"),
              names_sep = "_")
Joining, by = "sampleID"
met

split this into two data frames, one normalized by tissue amount and one not.

met_per_mg <- met %>% select(sampleID, block, genotype, trt, leaf_avg_std, starts_with("met_per_mg")) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>% column_to_rownames("sampleID")
met_amt <- met %>% select(sampleID,  block, genotype, trt, leaf_avg_std, starts_with("met_amt")) %>%
  as.data.frame() %>% column_to_rownames("sampleID")

met_per_mg_lme <- met_per_mg %>%
  mutate(trt=ifelse(str_detect(trt, "live"), "live", "blank_dead")) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols=starts_with("met"), names_to = "metabolite") %>%
  group_by(metabolite) %>%
  nest() %>%
  mutate(lme_trt=map(data, ~ lmer(value ~ trt + (1|block), data=.)),
         lme_leaf=map(data, ~ lmer(leaf_avg_std ~ value + (1|block), data=.)))

met_per_mg_lme_results<- met_per_mg_lme %>% mutate(broomtidy.trt = map(lme_trt, broom.mixed::tidy),
                                                   broomtidy.leaf = map(lme_leaf, broom.mixed::tidy)) %>%
  unnest(broomtidy.trt, broomtidy.leaf) %>%
  select(metabolite, term.trt=term, p.value.trt=p.value,
         term.leaf=term1, p.value.leaf=p.value1) %>%
  filter(term.trt=="trtlive",
         term.leaf=="value") %>%
  mutate(tissue=str_extract(metabolite,"(leaf|root)")) %>%
  group_by(tissue) %>%
  mutate(FDR.trt=p.adjust(p.value.trt, method = "fdr"),
         FDR.leaf=p.adjust(p.value.leaf, method = "fdr")) 
Warning: unnest() has a new interface. See ?unnest for details.
Try `df %>% unnest(c(broomtidy.trt, broomtidy.leaf))`, with `mutate()` if needed
met_per_mg_lme_results %>% ungroup() %>%
  summarize(sig.trt=sum(FDR.trt<0.1), sig.leaf=sum(FDR.leaf<0.1), sig.both=sum(FDR.trt<0.1&FDR.leaf<0.1), count=n())

met_per_mg_lme_results %>% filter(FDR.trt < 0.1 & FDR.leaf < 0.1) %>% 
  select(metabolite, FDR.trt, FDR.leaf) %>%
  arrange(min(.$sig.trt, .$sig.leaf))

                                             broomtidy.leaf = map(lme_leaf, broom.mixed::tidy)) %>%

         FDR.leaf=p.adjust(p.value.leaf, method = "fdr"))

met_per_mg_lme_results_nb <- met_per_mg_lme_nb %>% mutate(broomtidy.trt = map(lme_trt, broom.mixed::tidy),
                                                          broomtidy.leaf = map(lme_leaf, broom.mixed::tidy)) %>%
  unnest(broomtidy.trt, broomtidy.leaf) %>%
  select(metabolite, term.trt=term, p.value.trt=p.value,
         term.leaf=term1, p.value.leaf=p.value1) %>%
  filter(term.trt=="trtlive",
         term.leaf=="value") %>%
  mutate(tissue=str_extract(metabolite,"(leaf|root)")) %>%
  group_by(tissue) %>%
  mutate(FDR.trt=p.adjust(p.value.trt, method = "fdr"),
         FDR.leaf=p.adjust(p.value.leaf, method = "fdr"))

met_amt_lme_nb <- met_amt %>%
  filter(trt!="BLANK") %>%
  pivot_longer(cols=starts_with("met"), names_to = "metabolite") %>%
  group_by(metabolite) %>%
  nest() %>%
  mutate(lme_trt=map(data, ~ lmer(value ~ trt + (1|block), data=.)),
         lme_leaf=map(data, ~ lmer(leaf_avg_std ~ value + (1|block), data=.)))
